SUMMARY: 

OSM is announcing the receipt of a proposed amendment to the Iowa permanent regulatory program (hereinafter, the
``Iowa program'') under the Surface Mining Control and Reclamation Act of 1977 (SMCRA). The proposed amendment consists
of changes to provisions of the Iowa regulations pertaining to rulemaking petitions, definitions, permit processing,
revisions, bonding, backfilling and grading, civil penalties, and individual civil penalties. The amendment is
intended to revise the Iowa program to be consistent with the corresponding Federal standards, to clarify ambiguities,
to and improve operational efficiency.



