In 1990, passenger cars, other highway vehicles, nonroad 
engines and equipment, and the transportation facilities used in 
interstate commerce produced from 53 to 63 percent of the total 
inventory of volatile organic compounds (VOCs) and from 70 to 94 
percent of the total inventory of oxides of nitrogen (NO

X

