A set of conflicts exist though, which may make it necessary for the FIP processes to also follow its own separate track.
For example, the local air boards are currently developing plans which not only meet the requirements of the Clean
Air Act Amendments of 1990, but also must meet the requirements of the California Clean Air Act. No such California
