Further, EPA believes that it is necessary for the FIPs to apply many of the controls to all three areas or in some cases,
state-wide. Reliance on the various local SIP processes to engage the public on these particular FIP measures would
make it difficult for interested parties to participate fully in all aspects of the dialogue, and could lead the public
