Standards for Construction and Farm Equipment. 
EPA is not generally assigning credit in the attainment 
demonstration for State (or local) regulations that have not 
already been approved as part of the SIP or are not now undergoing 
SIP approval. EPA's policy restricts State credit in either their 
attainment demonstrations or progress plans for reductions from 
measures that have not been submitted as approvable elements of the 
SIP. 
The principal reason for this policy has been to comply with 
section 110(a)(2)(A) of the Act, which requires that each SIP 
``include enforceable emission limitations and other control 
measures, means, or techniques (including economic incentives such 
as fees, marketable permits, and auctions of emissions rights), as 
well as schedules and timetables for compliance, as may be 
necessary or appropriate to meet the applicable requirements of 
this Act * * *.'' 
