The second type of authority, EPA's general authority under 
section 110(c), is essentially remedial, and EPA has broad power 
under that section to cure a defective state plan. Thus, in 
promulgating a FIP, EPA may exercise its own, independent 
regulatory authority under the Act in any way not clearly 
