Section 328 of the 1990 CAA Amendments required EPA to establish requirements to control air pollution from Outer
Continental Shelf (OCS) sources to attain and maintain federal and state ambient air quality standards and to comply
with part C of title I of the CAA. EPA promulgated the new OCS air regulations at 40 CFR part 55 (``Part 55'') on September
