(c) SierraPine Limited (Placer). Proposed 40 CFR 52.2961(q) controls the emissions from SierraPine Limited, a medium
density fiberboard plant in Placer County. Estimated uncontrolled emissions at the facility total approximately
306 tons of VOC per year, with the primary emissions points at three fiber dryers (178 tpy), two press vents (117 tpy),
and wood-waste fired boiler (11 tpy). The three wood fiber dryers use steam heat to dry the wood fibers but in the process
