press is then used to form the fiberboard. As the fiberboard is heated, VOCs (mostly formaldehyde) are driven off.
Currently all VOCs are emitted directly to the atmosphere. 

Based on a review of currently available controls, emissions from the dryers and vents could be reduced significantly
