EPA is proposing a flexible control strategy for the reduction of emissions from ships. This strategy would rely on
economic incentives to encourage operators of ships that frequently use Southern California ports to take the necessary
steps to reduce their emissions. Specifically, an emissions fee would be based on the type of emission control that
a particular ship used. Ship operators would be allowed (and encouraged) to reduce the fees which would be applied
