appropriate for permit fee calculation, or whether they should 
be further subdivided to reflect differences in emissions or use 
within a class (e.g., some of these classes, such as 2-cycle 
outboards, could be further subdivided based on horsepower to 
reflect the very wide range of horsepower, usage, and total 
emissions that might be seen within the class). 

Average excess emissions per engine would be calculated 
separately for each engine class based on the difference between 
the sum of average HC and NO

X

 emissions for pre-standard engines 
and the sum of average HC and NO

X

 emissions for engines meeting 
the appropriate new standard. Total average excess emissions 
