allow significant growth. Electrification, under strong 
consideration for at least some South Coast lines would greatly 
facilitate compliance and reductions. EPA requests comment on 
what types of engines or strategies may be required to comply 
with this program. 

EPA does not anticipate that additional measures of 
reduction will be required at this time. However several 
options, which EPA could not finalize due to technological 
issues, but could develop later as provided by section 182(e)(5) 
