The Sacramento area was classified as a ``Serious'' ozone nonattainment area based on a design value of .16 ppm recorded
at the Folsom station. This was based on 1987-1989 data; the 1990-1992 value was also .16 ppm. Exceedances
of the ozone NAAQS occur in the Sacramento area about 15 times per year.
In order to simulate air quality for the SIP and other planning needs, CARB and the Sacramento local agencies started
planning the Sacramento Area Ozone Study (SAOS) early in 1989, with intensive data collection performed during the
