. 
EPA is proposing that enhanced I/M be used in the designated 
California FIP areas of Sacramento, Los Angeles, and Ventura. 
EPA is proposing to limit the geographic scope of the I/M-based 
recall program to the FIP areas. EPA does not believe it would 
be appropriate to apply the I/M-based recall program to areas not 
having full enhanced I/M based on the I/M 240 test. 
However, vehicles from outside the three FIP areas do impact 
air quality in the three FIP areas. Therefore, EPA requests 
comment on the option of including the vehicles tested in 
qualifying enhanced I/M 240 test programs in other nonattainment 
areas in California in the I/M-based recall program. The test 
results from such vehicles would then also be used to determine 
