 The Agency will provide manufacturers with cumulative test 
results on their engine families on a monthly basis. 
Additionally EPA will notify vehicle manufacturers, by letter, 
within thirty days after the rate of failure meets or exceeds the 
liability threshold. Manufacturers' responsibility for repairs 
begins 30 days after EPA sends notification. 
I/M personnel will notify owners of failing vehicles, when 
vehicles are brought in for emissions testing, with whom 
responsibility for repair lies. Vehicle owners must be informed 
