the remote reservoir is not being used, cleaned, or repaired; 

(B) Direct solvent flow in a manner that will prevent liquid solvent from splashing outside of the remote reservoir
cold cleaner; 

(C) Not degrease porous or absorbent materials, such as cloth, leather, wood, or rope; and 

(D) Use only solvent containers free of all liquid leaks. Auxiliary equipment, such as pumps, pipelines, or flanges,
shall not have any liquid leaks, visible tears, or cracks. Any liquid leak, visible tear, or crack detected shall be
repaired within one calendar day, or the leaking section of the remote reservoir cold cleaner shall be drained of all
solvent and shut down until it is replaced or repaired. 

(iv) 

Storage and disposal. 

(A) All VOC-containing solvents shall be stored in non-absorbent, non-leaking containers which shall be kept closed
at all times except when filling or emptying. 

