person may comply by using an emission control system in association with the solvent cleaning operation regulated
by this section provided: 

(A) The emission control system maintains a capture efficiency of at least 90%, by weight, of the emissions generated
by the solvent cleaning operation and a destruction or removal efficiency of at least 95% by weight; or 

(B) The emission control system maintains a capture efficiency of at least 90%, by weight, of the emissions generated
by the solvent cleaning operation and the output of the control system is less than 50 parts per million (ppm) calculated
as carbon with no dilution; or 

(C) The emission control system meets the requirements of an applicable source-specific section of the Federal or
federally approved State Implementation Plan. 


