CARB certified vapor recovery system 

is any Phase I or Phase II vapor recovery system which has been certified by the California Air Resources Board (CARB)
pursuant to section 41954 of the California Health and Safety Code as capable of recovering or processing displaced
gasoline vapors to an efficiency of ninety-five (95) percent or greater. For the purpose of this section, the term
