Agricultural burning

 means open outdoor fires used in the 
following operations: agricultural operations; forest 
management; range improvement; improvement of land for wildlife 
and game habitat; disease or pest prevention; operation or 
maintenance of a system for the delivery of water used in any 
agricultural operation, forest management, range improvement, 
land improvement for wildlife and game habitat, and disease or 
pest prevention operation; wildland vegetation management. 


Agricultural operations

