receiving the notice by registered mail, a late penalty will be 
assessed at the time the vehicle is presented for confirmatory 
testing, or at the time of the next regularly scheduled test, 
whichever comes first. The late penalty is a $10 fee for each 
full week beyond the 30-day deadline after initial notification 
of the need for confirmatory testing. 
